### Get all images. Each request **MUST** be delimited by a triple hash

# This is a comment

GET http://localhost:3000/api/images HTTP/1.1


### A second example. Each request **MUST** be delimited by a triple hash

POST http://localhost:3000/api/test HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json # Content-Type header is a must if you're sending JSON

{
  "a": 1,
  "b": 2
}


### Api Image

GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/69aa55775d0055a033b181c0 HTTP/1.1


### Api Image Invalid image due to invalid imageID

GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/helloSilus HTTP/1.1


### API image invlaid due to no such image exist

GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/69aa55775d0055a033b181cj HTTP/1.1


### UpdateName: Actual working one

PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69aa55775d0055a033b181c0 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "updatedName"
}


### UpdateName: Too long name

PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/hi HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "loremdwaidwajkldwajdklwajdklwadwaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa"
}


### UpdateName: Missing name attribute

PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/hi HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "helloSilus": "loremdwaidwajkldwajdklwajdklwadwaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa"
}


### UpdateName: Invalid id

PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/hi HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "hi"
}
